<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1918-12-05T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1918-12-05T12:00:00-05:00" n="85" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d85">
                        <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 182/17: Telegram</note>
                        <head>
                            <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Acting Secretary of
                                    State</gloss> to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of State</gloss>
                            </hi>
                        </head>
                        <opener>
                            <dateline rendition="#right">
                                <placeName>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Washington</hi>
                                </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1918-12-05T12:00:00-05:00">December 5,
                                1918—noon</date>.<lb/>[Received 3:30 p.m.]</dateline>
                        </opener>
                        <p>2. From <persName corresp="#p_HCEM1">Colonel House</persName>, December
                            [4]. December 16th would be perfectly convenient so far as the British
                            Government are concerned for the holding of the first meeting of the
                            inter-Allied Conference. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName>
                            adds that <persName corresp="#p_CGEB1">Clemenceau</persName> expressed
                            the view that December 16th might prove too early. <persName corresp="#p_BAJ1">Balfour</persName> suggests that it may be wise to
                            allow a few days for informal discussions before the actual meeting of
                            the Conference.</p>
                        <closer>
                            <signed>
                                <persName corresp="#p_PFL1">
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Polk</hi>
                                </persName>
                            </signed>
                        </closer>
                    </div>
                    </body></text></TEI>